OL,3,CJury in Gerry Adams' libel case to
OL,4,Cresume deliberations on Friday morning
OL,6,FThe remaining 11 members continued
OL,7,Ftheir consideration of the issues
OL,8,Fbefore being sent home at 17.10.
OL,10,FThey are tasked with determining
OL,11,Fwhether the words in the BBC spotlight
OL,12,Fprogramme and accompanying article, on
OL,13,Fwhich Mr Adams brought the complaint,
OL,14,Fmean that he sanctioned and approved
OL,15,Fthe murder of Mr Donaldson.
OL,17,FMr Owens said they were to consider
OL,18,Fwhether it was "more likely than not"
OL,19,Fthat a "hypothetical reasonable
OL,20,Freader" would take that meaning from
OL,21,Fthe words.
