OL,3,CJury in Gerry Adams' libel case to
OL,4,Cresume deliberations on Friday morning
OL,6,FHowever, if the jury find that the
OL,7,Fmeaning of the words was that Mr Adams
OL,8,Fhad sanctioned the killing, they are
OL,9,Fthen tasked with considering whether
OL,10,Fthe BBC broadcast and published the
OL,11,Fwords in good faith ` and whether it
OL,12,Fwas fair and reasonable to do so.
OL,14,FThe members of the jury have heard
OL,15,Farguments about the seriousness of the
OL,16,Fallegation, the attempts made to
OL,17,Fcorroborate it, and details on the
OL,18,Fproduction of the programme.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G7/10
