OL,3,CJury in Gerry Adams' libel case to
OL,4,Cresume deliberations on Friday morning
OL,6,FIf the jury finds that the BBC was
OL,7,Ffair and reasonable and had acted in
OL,8,Fgood faith, it effectively finds in
OL,9,Ffavour of the broadcaster and will not
OL,10,Fgo on to consider damages.
OL,12,FIf, however, the jury finds that the
OL,13,FBBC had either not acted in good
OL,14,Ffaith, or if it had not been fair and
OL,15,Freasonable in its actions, it can then
OL,16,Fconsider damages.
OL,18,FIt is tasked with assessing "general
OL,19,Fdamages" and has been told that the
OL,20,Fpurpose of this is for the injury to
OL,21,Fthe reputation.
